@startuml
title Loo-Cast Ecosystem Context (Ownership Mapping + Dual Gate + Transparency)
left to right direction

' =========================
' DARK MODE REVIEW THEME
' =========================

skinparam backgroundColor #121417
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName JetBrains Mono
skinparam defaultFontColor #f3f5f7
skinparam linetype polyline
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam nodesep 70
skinparam ranksep 80

skinparam component {
  BackgroundColor #26313c
  BorderColor #7c8b9b
  FontColor #ffffff
  RoundCorner 10
  BackgroundColor<<Platform>> #234057
  BorderColor<<Platform>> #77b7e8
  BackgroundColor<<Runtime>> #2f3f2a
  BorderColor<<Runtime>> #96c37a
  BackgroundColor<<External>> #382d43
  BorderColor<<External>> #b492d8
  BackgroundColor<<Governance>> #3a3726
  BorderColor<<Governance>> #d6c57f
}

skinparam actor {
  BackgroundColor #2b3742
  BorderColor #98a7b8
  FontColor #ffffff
}

skinparam package {
  BackgroundColor #1b2128
  BorderColor #5f6a75
  FontColor #ffffff
}

skinparam cloud {
  BackgroundColor #382d43
  BorderColor #b492d8
  FontColor #ffffff
}

skinparam database {
  BackgroundColor #2b353f
  BorderColor #7c8b9b
  FontColor #ffffff
}

skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #2a3138
  BorderColor #8b98a6
  FontColor #f3f5f7
}

skinparam ArrowColor #79b8ff
skinparam ArrowFontColor #f3f5f7

actor "Root Developer" as RootDev
actor "Namespace Owner\n(GitHub + Steam identity)" as Owner
actor "Mod Developer" as ModDev
actor "Submission Requester\n(anyone)" as Submitter
actor "Player" as Player

package "Loo-Cast Platform (Internal Governance Domain)" #1d2a34 {
  component "SDK\n(Contract + Tooling)" as SDK <<Platform>>
  component "Canonical CI Publisher" as CI <<Governance>>
  component "Registry Verification Gate" as RegGate <<Governance>>
  component "Automated + Manual Review Pipeline" as Review <<Governance>>
  database "Namespace Ownership Mapping Index\n(active + alias history)" as OwnershipMapIndex <<Governance>>
  database "Version Ownership Mapping Snapshots\n(immutable per version)" as VersionOwnershipSnapshots <<Governance>>
  database "Version Integrity Tuple Store\n(immutable per version)" as VersionTupleStore <<Governance>>
  database "Transparency Log\n(append-only hash-chained events)" as TLog <<Governance>>
  database "Registry Version Index\n(immutable record + mutable status)" as Registry <<Governance>>
  database "Artifact Archive\n(content-addressed)" as ArtifactArchive <<Governance>>
  database "Source + Asset Archive\n(git snapshot archive)" as SourceArchive <<Governance>>
  component "Launcher" as Launcher <<Platform>>
  component "Engine Host" as Engine <<Runtime>>
}

package "External Infrastructure (Out-of-Process)" #2d2537 {
  cloud "Steam\n(Identity + Distribution)" as Steam <<External>>
  cloud "GitHub\n(Source Hosting)" as GitHub <<External>>
}

RootDev -[#7ecbff]-> SDK : Define core_engine + core_mod
ModDev -[#7ecbff]-> SDK : Develop mods

ModDev -[#7ecbff]-> GitHub : Push source + tag
GitHub -[#9de37e]-> CI : release ref
CI -[#9de37e]-> Steam : publish package bytes
CI -[#9de37e]-> RegGate : CI provenance manifest
Owner -[#7ecbff]-> RegGate : register namespace ownership mapping\n(GitHub + Steam)
Submitter -[#7ecbff]-> RegGate : release request + logged-in identities
Steam -[#9de37e]-> RegGate : artifact bytes by ref
GitHub -[#9de37e]-> RegGate : source snapshot by ref
RegGate -[#9de37e]-> OwnershipMapIndex : verify namespace ownership mapping\n(active alias match)
RegGate -[#9de37e]-> VersionOwnershipSnapshots : persist version ownership snapshot
RegGate -[#9de37e]-> ArtifactArchive : persist verified bytes
RegGate -[#9de37e]-> SourceArchive : persist verified source
RegGate -[#9de37e]-> VersionTupleStore : persist immutable version tuple
RegGate -[#9de37e]-> Registry : append immutable record\n(status=pending_review)
RegGate -[#9de37e]-> TLog : append admission event
RegGate -[#9de37e]-> Review : trigger review
Review -[#9de37e]-> Registry : status -> active/deprecated/banned
Review -[#9de37e]-> TLog : append review/moderation event

Player -[#7ecbff]-> Launcher : Configure modpack
Launcher -[#9de37e]-> Registry : Resolve public DAG + status
Launcher -[#9de37e]-> ArtifactArchive : Fetch artifact by digest
Launcher -[#9de37e]-> VersionOwnershipSnapshots : verify version ownership snapshot
Launcher -[#9de37e]-> VersionTupleStore : verify tuple consistency
Launcher -[#f5c57a]-> Engine : Launch validated set

RootDev -[hidden]-> ModDev
Owner -[hidden]-> ModDev
ModDev -[hidden]-> Submitter
ModDev -[hidden]-> Player
GitHub -[hidden]- Steam
SDK -[hidden]- CI
CI -[hidden]- RegGate
RegGate -[hidden]- Review
OwnershipMapIndex -[hidden]- TLog
VersionOwnershipSnapshots -[hidden]- Registry
VersionTupleStore -[hidden]- Registry
Registry -[hidden]- ArtifactArchive
Launcher -[hidden]- Engine

legend right
|= Edge Color |= Meaning |
|<#7ecbff>| Authoring / user intent |
|<#9de37e>| Governance / distribution data flow |
|<#f5c57a>| Runtime handoff |
endlegend

note bottom of Registry
Public consumption rule:
pending_review versions are not surfaced to launcher consumers.
end note

note bottom of OwnershipMapIndex
Ownership mapping policy:
namespace identity is bound to
GitHub repo ownership + Steam publisher identity.
Ownership transfer is recorded via alias history.
end note

note bottom of VersionOwnershipSnapshots
Historical rule:
each admitted version stores its own immutable
ownership mapping snapshot.
Old versions resolve against old snapshots.
end note

note bottom of VersionTupleStore
Consistency rule:
each admitted version stores an immutable tuple
(artifact_digest, source_digest, ownership_snapshot_id, ci_provenance_id).
launcher verifies tuple consistency before runtime handoff.
end note

note right of SDK
Includes contract authoring,
build, and publishing tooling.
end note

note right of RegGate
Second hard gate after CI:
admission requires ownership mapping, hash, and DAG verification.
end note

note right of Launcher
Launcher validates status/hashes/DAG
against registry and archive data before runtime handoff.
end note

note right of Engine
Deterministic boot:
core_mod first, then topological mod load.
end note

@enduml
